docs.abstract: “It’s like if you were told that there’s going to be a world-conquering dictator and it’s Mr. Bean.”
docs.snippet: “It’s like if you were told that there’s going to be a world-conquering dictator and it’s Mr. Bean.”
docs.lead_paragraph: A few days after a lawyer used ChatGPT to write a brief filled with made-up cases, a group of A.I. experts released a letter warning of the “risk of extinction” from the technology. But will A.I. ever be good enough to pose such a threat?

headline.main: A.I.’s Inner Conflict, Nvidia Joins the Trillion-Dollar Club, and Hard Questions

byline.original: By Kevin Roose, Casey Newton, Davis Land, Rachel Cohn, Jen Poyant, Alyssa Moxley, Dan Powell, Elisheba Ittoop, Marion Lozano, Sophia Lanman and Rowan Niemisto

docs.abstract: Reports that the White House may clamp down on sales of semiconductors that power artificial intelligence capabilities sent tech stocks diving.
docs.snippet: Reports that the White House may clamp down on sales of semiconductors that power artificial intelligence capabilities sent tech stocks diving.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Biden administration is weighing additional curbs on China’s ability to access critical technology, including restricting the sale of high-end chips used to power artificial intelligence, according to five people familiar with the deliberations.

headline.main: Biden Administration Weighs Further Curbs on Sales of A.I. Chips to China
headline.print_headline: U.S. May Cut China’s Path To A.I. Chips

byline.original: By Ana Swanson, David McCabe and Michael Crowley

docs.abstract: Global markets edged higher as the prospect of the United States defaulting on its debt grows more remote.
docs.snippet: Global markets edged higher as the prospect of the United States defaulting on its debt grows more remote.
docs.lead_paragraph: The debt-ceiling deal is a step closer to becoming law after its breezy passage in the House last night, making the prospect of a U.S. default all the more remote. Investors expressed relief, sending global markets and U.S. stock futures higher this morning.

headline.main: Investors Exhale as Debt Limit Deal Clears a Big Hurdle

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Ravi Mattu, Bernhard Warner, Sarah Kessler, Michael J. de la Merced, Lauren Hirsch and Ephrat Livni

docs.abstract: Jensen Huang, the C.E.O. of Nvidia, is transforming a black leather jacket into a symbol of the A.I. paradigm shift.
docs.snippet: Jensen Huang, the C.E.O. of Nvidia, is transforming a black leather jacket into a symbol of the A.I. paradigm shift.
docs.lead_paragraph: There’s a new tech titan in town and he’s preparing to enter the pantheon. How do we know?

headline.print_headline: Silicon Valley Has a New Style Star

docs.abstract: Shares in the semiconductor giants Nvidia and AMD fell on a report that the Biden Administration is weighing new restrictions on A.I.-related exports.
docs.snippet: Shares in the semiconductor giants Nvidia and AMD fell on a report that the Biden Administration is weighing new restrictions on A.I.-related exports.
docs.lead_paragraph: Shares in high-flying chipmakers like Nvidia and AMD were down in premarket trading today, after The Wall Street Journal reported that the Biden administration is weighing new restrictions on exporting artificial intelligence-related semiconductors to China.

headline.main: The A.I. Chips War Could Heat Up This Summer

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Ravi Mattu, Bernhard Warner, Sarah Kessler, Michael J. de la Merced and Lauren Hirsch
